                    <p> The Alabama native's highest-selling letter, penned in 1999 about the civil rights movement, sold for $4,753, the auction house said. In it, she thanks Leapard for providing her with civil rights icon Vivian Malone's autograph. </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> While Lee — a Pulitzer Prize winner in 1961 — was famously reclusive, her writing remains as popular as ever. Her last novel, &quot;Go Set a Watchman,&quot; was released last summer and <a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/books/go-set-watchman-new-harper-lee-novel-sells-more-1m-n395101">sold a record-breaking 1.1 million copies</a> in its first week in North America. </p>
                
              
